{"lemma":"ثَجَّ","slug":"ثَجَّ","root":"ث.ج.ج","root_slug":"ث-ج-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ج-ج","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"ثَجَجْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"ثَجَجْتِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"ثَجَجْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"ثَجَجْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"ثَجَجْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"ثَجَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"ثَجَّت","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"ثَجّا","in_corpus":true,"count":5,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"ثَجَّتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"ثَجُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"ثَجَجْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَثُجّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَثْجُج","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَثُجِّينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَثُجِّي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَثُجّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَثُجّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَثُجُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَثُجُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَثْجُجْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَثُجّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَثْجُج","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَثُجّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَثْجُج","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَثُجّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَثُجّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَثُجّا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَثُجّانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَثُجُّوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَثُجُّونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَثْجُجْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَثُجّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَثُجّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"ثَجَجْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"ثَجَجْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":5,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4348"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4348","headword_ar":"ثَجَّ","root":"vj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaj~N","text_ar":"ثَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vajiyjN","text_ar":"ثَجِيجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vujuwjN","text_ar":"ثُجُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured forth vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(much water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anvj~","text_ar":"انثجّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavajovaja","text_ar":"تَثَجْثَجَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same. (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaj~N","text_ar":"ثَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the blood of a victim brought for sacrifice to the sacred territory of Mekkeh. (S, K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaj~ahu","text_ar":"ثَجَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaj~N","text_ar":"ثَجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to flow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured it forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) namely, water, (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and blood (S, A, Mgh, Msb) of a victim for sacrifice; (Mgh, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vajovajahu","text_ar":"ثَجْثَجَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Avj~hu","text_ar":"اثجّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also be used in the same sense. (TA.) Hence, (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoDalu AlHaj~i AlEaj~u wAlv~aj~u","text_ar":"اَفْضَلُ الحَجِّ العَجُّ والثَّجُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) a saying of Mohammad, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The most excellent of the actions of the pilgrimage are"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the raising of the voice in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talobiyap","text_ar":"تَلْبِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lbY","text_ar":"لبى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the shedding of the blood of the victims brought for sacrifice to the sacred territory."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","Msb","K","TA","S","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AB%D8%AC/","headword_ar":"ثج","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_10","lexicon_en":"Abū Mūsā al-Madīnī, al-Majmūʿ al-Mughīth fī Gharībay al-Qurʾān wa-l-Ḥadīth (d. 1185 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المجموع المغيث في غريبي القرآن والحديث لأبو موسى المديني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17709#edbaed","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">(ثج)</span><span> - في حَدِيثِ رُقَيْقَة : \"اكتَظَّ الوَادِي بِثَجِيجِه\".</span><br><span>: أي بمَثْجُوجِه ومَصْبُوبِه، وما سَالَ منه.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17709#999b78","body_html":"ثج<br>الثَّجُ: شِدَّةُ انْصِبَابِ المَطَرِ والدَّم، مَطَرٌ ثُجّاجٌ.<br>والثّجَّةُ: الرَّوْضَةُ.<br>ووَطْبٌ مُثَجَّجٌ: صَرِدٌ. وهو من الألبانِ: ما لم يَجْتَمِعْ زُبْدُه. والثَّجِيْجَة: مِثْلُ القَفِيْخَةِ وهما زُبْدَةُ اللَّبَن التي تَلْزَقُ باليَدِ والسِّقاءِ.<br>وتَثَجْثَجَ الماءُ: بمعنى ثَجَّ."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17709#83a36f","body_html":"<h3>ثج</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> ثَجَّ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـِ (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> ثَجٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) or ثَجِيجٌ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) or ثُجُوجٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) It (water) flowed: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or poured forth vehemently, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) or much: or, as some say, it (much water) poured forth: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) and ↓ انثجّ and ↓ تَثَجْثَجَ signify the same. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) ثَجٌّ also signifies The flowing of the blood of a victim brought for sacrifice to the sacred territory of Mekkeh. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> ثَجَّهُ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> ثَجٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) He made it to flow; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr> <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) poured it forth; (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>;) namely, water, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and blood (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>) of a victim for sacrifice; (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>;) as also ↓ ثَجْثَجَهُ; and ↓ اثجّهُ may also be used in the same sense. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) Hence, (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) أَفْضَلُ الحَجِّ العَجُّ والثَّجُّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) a saying of Mohammad, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) meaning The most excellent of the actions of the pilgrimage are (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>) the raising of the voice in the تَلْبِيَة [see 2 in art. لبى] and the shedding of the blood of the victims brought for sacrifice to the sacred territory. (<abbr title=\"The Mughrib of al-Mutarrizī\">Mgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) 4 أَثْجَ3َ see 1.<span class=\"sense\">7</span> إِنْثَجَ3َ see 1.<br><br>R. <abbr title=\"quadriliteral-radical verb, فِعْلٌ رُبَاعِيٌّ\">Q.</abbr> 1 see 1.<br><br>R. <abbr title=\"quadriliteral-radical verb, فِعْلٌ رُبَاعِيٌّ\">Q.</abbr> 2 see 1.<br><br>حَلَبَ فِيهِ ثَجًّا He milked into it milk abundantly flowing. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr> from a <abbr title=\"tradition (hadith), حَدِيْثٌ\">trad.</abbr>) ثَجُوجٌ A source yielding abundance of water. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> See also ثَجَّاجٌ.<br><br>ثَجِيجٌ [originally an <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> (see 1)] A torrent, or flow. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) So in the saying, أَتَانَا الوَادِى<br><br>بِثَجِيجِهِ [The valley brought us its torrent, or flow]. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> The sound of the pouring forth of water. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> See also ثَجَّاجٌ.<br><br>ثَجَّاجٌ Water pouring forth vehemently: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) or poured forth; as also ↓ ثَجُوجٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or flowing: (<abbr title=\"Maqāmat al-Ḥarīrī, the Commentary on; 2nd edit, of Paris\">Har</abbr> p. 138:) or flowing much: (Id. p. 393:) and rain pouring forth vehemently; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) as also ↓ ثَجِيجٌ and ↓ مِثَجٌّ: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) and blood poured forth: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) and a cloud pouring forth. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) Applied to water [or rain, and to blood,] it may have the meaning of a <abbr title=\"passive participial noun, إِسْمُ مَفْعُولٍ\">pass. part. n.</abbr>, or, which is preferable, that of an <abbr title=\"active participial noun, اِسْمُ فَاعِلٍ\">act. part. n.</abbr> (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [Hence,] فُلَانٌ غَيْثُهُ وَبَحْرُهُ عَجَّاجٌ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) [<abbr title=\"literally\">lit.</abbr> Such a one, his rain is such as pours forth vehemently, and his sea is noisy, or copious: meaning such a one is abundant in bounty or munificence]. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) مِثَجٌّ: see ثَجَّاجٌ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Also, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or خَطِيبٌ مِثَجٌّ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) An eloquent, or able, speaker or orator; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) who pours forth a copious flow of words. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.)"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_31","lexicon_en":"Al-Rāghib al-Isfahānī, al-Mufradāt fī Gharīb al-Qurʾān (d. c. 1109 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المفردات في غريب القرآن للراغب الأصفهاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=17709#ab16d5","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">ثج</span><span>َ</span><br><span>يقال: ثَجَّ الماء، وأتى الوادي بِثَجِيجِه. قال الله تعالى: وَأَنْزَلْنا مِنَ الْمُعْصِراتِ ماءً ثَجَّاجاً</span><br><span>[النبأ/ 14] ، وفي الحديث: «أفضل الحجّ العجّ والثَّجُّ» أي: رفع الصوت بالتلبية، وإسالة دم الهدي.</span>"}]}}